  "local_port": 41000,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which companies in Silicon Valley hire/are likely to hire computational biologists?",
  "response": "Silicon Valley is home to a wide range of companies that hire computational biologists due to the growing importance of bioinformatics, genomics, and biotech innovation. Here are some types of companies and specific examples that are likely to hire computational biologists:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Biotechnology Companies**\n   - **Genentech**: A leader in biotech, actively uses computational biology for drug discovery and genomics.\n   - **Gilead Sciences**: Focuses on antiviral and oncology research, employing computational biologists for data analysis.\n   - **Amgen**: Engages in computational biology for therapeutic development and biomarker discovery.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Pharmaceutical Companies**\n   - **Roche (Genentech\u2019s parent company)**: Utilizes computational biology for drug development and personalized medicine.\n   - **Janssen (Johnson & Johnson)**: Invests in computational biology for immunology and oncology research.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Genomics and Precision Medicine Companies**\n   - **23andMe**: Leverages computational biology for genetic data analysis and population genomics.\n   - **Illumina**: A leader in DNA sequencing technology, hires computational biologists for bioinformatics and genomic analysis.\n   - **Invitae**: Focuses on genetic testing and employs computational biologists for variant interpretation and data analysis.\n\n---\n\n### **4. AI and Data-Driven Health Companies**\n   - **Verily (Alphabet\u2019s life sciences arm)**: Works on health data analysis and employs computational biologists for projects in precision medicine.\n   - **Tempus**: Uses computational biology to analyze clinical and molecular data for cancer treatment.\n   - **Deep Genomics**: Combines AI and computational biology for drug discovery and genetic medicine.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Tech Giants with Health and Biotech Divisions**\n   - **Google Health**: Engages in computational biology for health data analysis and research.\n   - **Microsoft Research**: Works on computational biology projects in genomics and healthcare.\n   - **Amazon Web Services (AWS)**: Provides cloud solutions for bioinformatics and genomics, often hiring computational biologists for tool development.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Startups and Emerging Companies**\n   - **Recursion Pharmaceuticals**: Uses computational biology and AI for drug discovery.\n   - **Freenome**: Focuses on cancer detection using computational biology and machine learning.\n   - **Insitro**: Combines machine learning and computational biology for drug development.\n   - **Sana Biotechnology**: Works on cell engineering and regenerative medicine, employing computational biologists.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Research Institutions and Academic Labs**\n   - **Stanford University**: Many labs hire computational biologists for research in genomics, systems biology, and bioinformatics.\n   - **UC Berkeley**: Collaborates with industry partners and hires computational biologists for interdisciplinary research.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Bioinformatics and Software Companies**\n   - **DNAnexus**: Provides cloud-based bioinformatics platforms, hiring computational biologists for tool and algorithm development.\n   - **Seven Bridges Genomics**: Focuses on bioinformatics and computational biology for genomic data analysis.\n\n---\n\n### **9. Venture Capital-Backed Biotech Firms**\n   Silicon Valley is a hub for VC-backed biotech companies, many of which hire computational biologists early in their growth.\n\n---\n\n### **Skills and Trends**\nTo increase your chances of being hired, focus on skills like:\n   - Genomics and bioinformatics\n   - Machine learning and AI in biology\n   - Data science and big data analytics\n   - Programming (Python, R, etc.)\n   - Knowledge of sequencing technologies (e.g., NGS)\n\n---\n\nSilicon Valley\u2019s ecosystem is highly interdisciplinary, so computational biologists often find roles in companies that blend biology, technology, and data science. Networking and staying updated on industry trends can also help identify emerging opportunities.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
